During Fire Prevention Week, President Biden reaffirms the commitment to preventing fires and mitigating damage. The article highlights the devastating impact of wildfires, with tens of thousands of fires burning over two million acres and causing loss of life, destruction of homes and natural resources. The Biden Administration's Investing in America Agenda includes significant climate investments, such as enhanced drought resilience, early wildfire detection, and post-wildfire restoration. The administration is also increasing resources for firefighters, including raising the Federal firefighter minimum wage to $15 an hour and creating programs to improve recruitment and retention. The article emphasizes the importance of fire prevention and safety, particularly in the kitchen. President Biden proclaims October 8-14, 2023, as Fire Prevention Week and calls on Americans to participate in activities to prevent fires and promote fire safety.